-- Porsche Blocks Staff Access to Facebook as Espionage Shield, WiWo Reports
-- B y   A n d r e a s   C r e m e r
-- 2010-10-09T11:05:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-09/porsche-blocks-staff-access-to-facebook-as-espionage-shield-wiwo-reports.html
Porsche SE  has blocked employees’
access to Facebook Inc. to shield the luxury carmaker against
industrial espionage,  Wirtschaftswoche  reported, citing Rainer
Benne, the company’s head of security.  Stuttgart, Germany-based Porsche barred the use of Facebook
at company workstations to prevent foreign intelligence services
from spying on workers, the magazine quoted Benne as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Andreas Cremer  in Paris via 
 acremer@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong at   kwong11@bloomberg.net . 